It is probably a good idea to actually measure the Delay time on an actual tx (and the usleep time) before changing this.  I am not sure what the equivalency is in reality.  I would not rely on code comments for accuracy.  With a UART, this shold be trivial to do using the systick times which should countdown at 9MHz:
Something like this should work:
volatile uint32_t *systick = (uint32_t *)0xe00e018;
volatile uint32_t *reload = (uint32_t *)0xe00e014;
while(1) {
    uint32_t count = 0;
    unsigned int i = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
        uint start = systick;
        Delay(100)
        uint32_t end = systick;
        uint32_t delta = end < start ? start - end : start + reload - end; //systick counts down from reload
        count += delta;
    }
    printf("Cycles: %d\n", count / 1000);
}

